COVID-19 spreads mainly among people who are in close contact (within about 6 feet) for a prolonged period. According to the CDC, spread happens when an infected person coughs, sneezes, or talks, and droplets from their mouth or nose are launched into the air and land in the mouths or noses of people nearby. The droplets can also be inhaled into the lungs. Recent studies indicate that people who are infected but do not have symptoms likely also play a role in the spread of COVID-19. This is why social distancing in a public place is very important. The following are some appropriate steps to implementing social distancing in a construction site: Also Read: General COVID-19 guidance for construction workers